name: Balance Board
instructions: Step:1 Place the balance board on a flat surface. | Step:2 Step onto the balance board with one foot, ensuring it is centered. | Step:3 Slowly shift your weight onto the foot on the balance board, keeping your core engaged. | Step:4 Maintain your balance and stability as you hold the position for a desired amount of time. | Step:5 Repeat the exercise with the other foot.

name: Single Leg Platform Slide
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with one foot on a platform or slide board. | Step:2 Bend your knee slightly and slide the foot on the platform backward, extending your leg. | Step:3 Keep your core engaged and maintain a straight posture throughout the movement. | Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position by sliding your foot back to the initial position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Exercise Ball Alternating Arm Ups
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing inwards and your arms extended down by your sides. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lift one arm up towards your shoulder, keeping your elbow slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arm back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement with the other arm. | Step:6 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push Up On Bosu Ball With Improved
instructions: Step:1 Place the bosu ball on the ground with the flat side facing up. | Step:2 Position yourself in a push-up position with your hands on the outer edges of the bosu ball. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower your body down towards the bosu ball by bending your elbows. Focus on improved movement. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball One Leg Prone Lower Body Rotation Fierce
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the stability ball with your hips resting on the ball and your legs extended straight behind you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground in front of you for support. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles to stabilize your body. | Step:4 Slowly lift one leg off the ground, keeping it straight and parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Rotate your leg outward, away from your body, while keeping your hips and upper body stable. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the end of the rotation, then slowly return your leg to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat the rotation with the other leg. Focus on fierce movement. | Step:8 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Alternating Arm Ups With Fast
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing inwards and your arms extended down by your sides. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lift one arm up towards your shoulder, keeping your elbow slightly bent. Perform with fast intensity. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arm back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement with the other arm. | Step:6 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Single Leg Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place the band around the ball of your left foot. | Step:2 Hold onto a stable object for balance if needed. | Step:3 Slowly raise your left heel off the ground, lifting your body weight onto the ball of your foot. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your left heel back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the right leg.

name: Exercise Ball Hug
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold the stability ball with both hands, hugging it close to your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core muscles and slowly lean back, keeping your back straight and your feet planted on the ground. | Step:4 Continue leaning back until you feel a stretch in your back muscles. | Step:5 Hold the position for a few seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Side Bend (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet shoulder-width apart and flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a weight in one hand and place your other hand on your hip. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly bend sideways towards the weighted side, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Exercise Ball Dip
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ball beside your hips, fingers pointing forward. | Step:3 Engage your triceps and push through your hands to lift your body off the ball, straightening your arms. | Step:4 Lower your body back down by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and position yourself facing down with your hands on the ball, shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs straight out behind you, balancing on your toes. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower your chest towards the ball by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Pike Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands on the floor and your shins resting on the stability ball. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your hips up towards the ceiling, rolling the ball towards your hands. | Step:3 Keep your legs straight and your body in a pike position, forming an inverted V shape. | Step:4 Bend your elbows and lower your upper body towards the floor, keeping your head in line with your hands. | Step:5 Push through your hands and extend your arms to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push Up On Bosu Ball
instructions: Step:1 Place the bosu ball on the ground with the flat side facing up. | Step:2 Position yourself in a push-up position with your hands on the outer edges of the bosu ball. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower your body down towards the bosu ball by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Single Leg Reverse Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place the band around the ball of your foot. | Step:2 Hold onto a stable object for balance. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heel off the ground, lifting your body weight onto the ball of your foot. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Prone Twist On Stability Ball
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying face down on a stability ball with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes touching the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or cross them over your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core muscles and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Rotate your torso to one side, bringing your shoulder towards your hip. Keep your hips and legs stable throughout the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the rotation to the other side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Seated Twist (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a weight plate or dumbbell with both hands close to your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly rotate your torso to one side, keeping your hips stable. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the rotation, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the rotation to the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Prone Leg Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a mat with your legs extended and your toes resting on top of the stability ball. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground, shoulder-width apart, and engage your core muscles. | Step:3 Keeping your legs straight, slowly lift them off the ground, using your lower back and glutes to raise them as high as possible. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up (Bosu Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Place the bosu ball on the ground with the flat side facing up. | Step:2 Position yourself in a push-up position with your hands on the outer edges of the bosu ball. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower your body down towards the bosu ball by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and position yourself facing down with your hands on the ball, shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs straight out behind you, balancing on your toes. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower your chest towards the ball by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball One Leg Prone Lower Body Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the stability ball with your hips resting on the ball and your legs extended straight behind you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground in front of you for support. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles to stabilize your body. | Step:4 Slowly lift one leg off the ground, keeping it straight and parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Rotate your leg outward, away from your body, while keeping your hips and upper body stable. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the end of the rotation, then slowly return your leg to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat the rotation with the other leg. | Step:8 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Gentle Prone Twist On Stability Ball
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying face down on a stability ball with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes touching the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or cross them over your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core muscles and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Rotate your torso to one side, bringing your shoulder towards your hip. Keep your hips and legs stable throughout the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 (gentle variation) Repeat the rotation to the other side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.
